race.description: Battery World Mornington & Frankston Maiden Plate
race.comment: AREAAN (8) motored home when finishing runner-up by a length at Sale 11 days ago, and steps up to a mile for the first time this prep, and she is overdue for her first win. On top. BOY FROM OZ (6) was at long odds when finishing second on debut here 9 days ago. He has a better draw this time, and the quick backup is a good sign. He can go one better, but don't expect another fancy price. Each way. ZAMPARINI SPIRIT (5) led up and faded quickly as the favourite at Cranbourne nearly 3 weeks ago. He has yet to race up to his good jumpout form from earlier in the season, but he is worth one more chance after a couple of gear changes since that run. Follow your money. DURNESS (10) was a touch weak in her initial prep and is bred to improve with more time. She resumes with 3 jumpouts under his belt, and she is capable of a top 4 finish fresh up. CHATEAU DANCER (9) was second fresh up at Pakenham nearly 5 weeks ago, and will pick up a win at short notice.
